PHASE 1 вЂ” PLAN:
- Ask clarifying questions first
- Write plan including React components,
  MongoDB schemas, and API endpoints
- Wait for my approval

PHASE 2 вЂ” BUILD BACKEND:
- Create Express server
- Connect MongoDB Atlas using .env
- Create Mongoose models
- Create all API routes with validation

PHASE 3 вЂ” BUILD FRONTEND:
- Initialize React with Vite
- Install tailwindcss axios react-router-dom
- Build all components and pages
- Connect to backend using Axios

PHASE 4 вЂ” TEST AUTOMATICALLY:
- Start backend server
- Start frontend dev server
- Run Playwright E2E tests
- Test all pages, forms, API calls
- Test mobile responsive layout

PHASE 5 вЂ” FIX AUTOMATICALLY:
- Fix any failing tests immediately
- Run all tests again after fixing
- Never deploy broken code

PHASE 7 вЂ” DEPLOY AUTOMATICALLY:

DEPLOYMENT PLATFORM: Vercel (completely free)
- Frontend: Vercel (React)
- Backend: Vercel (Python FastAPI)
- No credit card needed
- No manual steps needed

STEPS:
1. Create backend/vercel.json automatically
2. Run: vercel --prod --yes in backend folder
3. Get backend URL from output
4. Update frontend/.env.production with backend URL
5. Build frontend: npm run build
6. Run: vercel --prod --yes in frontend folder
7. Get frontend URL from output
8. Test both URLs end to end
9. Give me both live URLs

NEVER use Render, Railway, or Koyeb
ALWAYS use Vercel for all deployments

NEVER:
- Skip any phase
- Hardcode secrets
- Deploy without testing
- Leave incomplete code
- Ask me to do anything manually

